snippet.textDisplay:
I was vaccinated, and I am Autistic...I also was in the higher classes for Maths and Science, and see the world in ways non autistic people never will.
I solved problems in ways my teachers weren't looking for.
I've answered questions to films and tv that even the writers couldn't come up with answers for.
I've asked questions that no one I know of has ever asked.
I took and interest in the brain because I was interested in learning more about autism, I now know how the brain works.
I learn new skills on a daily basis just because.

I also took interests in different parts of the world, and now know how to make all sorts for food, from chapati's to sushi, from dahl to borscht.
If vaccines DO cause autism, then everyone should absolutely get vaccinated.
